<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at one’s worst • at the worst</xh5><p> <i>at one’s worst—</i>said of smb. in the worst or most undesirable state: Glennie was <u>at her worst</u>: still unchanged, wearing her dirty forenoon wrapper.</p><p> <i>at the worst—</i>in the worst possible case: If a man played long enough he was sure to win at last, or <u>at the worst</u>, not to come off a loser.</p> </entry>
